    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-07-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-09-07T20:52:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to reduce the federal tax refund of any taxpayer who owes a past-due, legally enforceable tax obligation to a local government by the amount of such obligation. Requires notice to the taxpayer of the refund reduction. </p> <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to permit disclosure of taxpayer information to agencies of states requesting refund offsets for tax debts owed to local governments. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend title 31, United States Code, to allow certain local tax debt to be collected through the reduction of Federal tax refunds.</title>
